Probabilistic Methods, Theory. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper specifically deals with the learning of probabilistic concepts, which are boolean functions that exhibit uncertain or probabilistic behavior. The authors develop efficient algorithms for learning natural classes of p-concepts and study the underlying theory of learning p-concepts.

Theory: The paper also focuses on developing a formal model of machine learning for probabilistic concepts that meets the demands of efficiency and generality. The authors study and develop in detail an underlying theory of learning p-concepts.
